<node id="&quot;UNINSURED MOTOR VEHICLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A land motor vehicle or trailer of any type that meets specific criteria regarding liability coverage, including lack of coverage, denial of coverage, insolvency of insurer, insufficient liability limits, unidentifiable owner/operator, or inadequate combined liability limits compared to uninsured/underinsured motorist coverage."&lt;SEP&gt;"A land motor vehicle or trailer with no applicable bodily injury liability bond or policy at the time of the accident."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle involved in an accident that has no liability insurance, making the operator or owner potentially liable."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle that meets the definition of uninsured but is excluded from that classification under specific conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"An uninsured motor vehicle is a vehicle without insurance coverage, whose operator or owner may be held legally liable."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c</data>
