<node id="&quot;ACTUAL CASH VALUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Actual cash value is defined as the replacement cost of a vehicle at the time of loss, minus physical depreciation based on standard business practices."&lt;SEP&gt;"Actual cash value is one of the four values used to determine the limit of liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"Actual cash value is the current market value of the auto, accounting for depreciation, and is used to determine the maximum liability limit."&lt;SEP&gt;"The current market value of a vehicle, adjusted for depreciation, used to determine maximum liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"The market value of the covered auto at the time of loss, calculated by subtracting depreciation from the replacement cost."&lt;SEP&gt;"The market value of the vehicle at the time of loss, minus depreciation."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ac858e839dd324c4b80701da2b87bd7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98ea72d43f9051dc6899f8d6aafcd9a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
