<node id="&quot;LIMIT OF LIABILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Maximum payment per insured person per accident."&lt;SEP&gt;"The insurer is not required to purchase a bond exceeding the policy limit."&lt;SEP&gt;"The limit of liability is a cap on the amount the insurer will pay for claims under the policy, and it will not be changed unless required by law."&lt;SEP&gt;"The limit of liability is the lowest of four values: actual cash value, replacement cost, repair cost, or stated amount."&lt;SEP&gt;"The limit of liability is the maximum amount that can be awarded by arbitrators."&lt;SEP&gt;"The limit of liability is the maximum amount the insurer will pay for covered claims."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount an insurer will pay for a covered loss."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount an insurer will pay for bodily injury under a policy; if below the state-mandated minimum, the vehicle is considered uninsured."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount an insurer will pay under a policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer is liable for under this policy, used to determine the share of loss."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer is liable for, used to calculate the proportionate share."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for a covered loss, as defined in the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for a covered loss, expressed as a percentage of the actual cash value of the covered auto at the time of loss."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for claims under this coverage, which applies to defense costs and judgments."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for each insured person injured in any one accident, regardless of the number of claims, vehicles, or policies involved."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for liability coverage, as stated on the declarations page, regardless of the number of claims, covered autos, insured persons, lawsuits, vehicles, or premiums."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for loss to an auto under Part IV is capped by the actual cash value of the auto, including custom parts and equipment."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for medical expenses per insured person per accident."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount the insurer will pay."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-245fa605e8e023a6acdcf8c36c35930e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8918d81dfdf6055a12c8c1d621356d08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-798fdf9e8255810d437349cea720f315</data>
</node>
