  <data key="d2">chunk-2e3e05ae8cb995bb756587490f5512f4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;GOOD FAITH&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The principle that both parties must act honestly and fairly in insurance dealings."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRAILER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A trailer has a liability limit equal to the amount shown on the declarations page. If not listed, the limit is $500."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trailer is a non-motorized vehicle designed to be towed on public roads by an auto, including farm wagons or implements, and not used for commercial, office, store, display, or passenger purposes."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trailer is a vehicle that can be towed and is included in the definition of 'Insured person' when struck by it."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trailer is a vehicle towed by an auto and is covered under this policy, with accidents arising from its ownership, maintenance, or use being covered."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trailer is not covered under this policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trailer not listed on the declarations page, which may be covered under the policy with excess terms."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trailer owned by the policyholder is a covered auto."&lt;SEP&gt;"A trailer used on land, which may be uninsured."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cd680372852b670779cd9ab038f278e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ea57b3201f9d42edca3669635573a74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55b66238ae6adb6999a975e6b7f7834c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DOCUMENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A document must be signed by the insured person agreeing to reimbursement."&lt;SEP&gt;"The insured must sign a document agreeing to reimburse the insurer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-69d3b921f75f85252f4c9cdeaa3141bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OTHER SOURCES OF RECOVERY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A section explaining that the insured may seek recovery from other sources, such as the at-fault driver."&lt;SEP&gt;"Alternative ways to recover losses outside the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Other sources of recovery refer to alternative insurance or financial resources that may cover the same loss."&lt;SEP&gt;"Refers to alternative means of recovering losses outside of the insurance policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e4f63404276c60a3d82c899176c55043&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e3e05ae8cb995bb756587490f5512f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREJUDGMENT INTEREST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Prejudgment interest is interest awarded against an insured person before a judgment is entered, and is included in the damages covered by this policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Prejudgment interest is interest awarded to a claimant before a judgment is made, and is included in damages."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-55b66238ae6adb6999a975e6b7f7834c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;JUDGE OF A COURT OF RECORD&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A judicial officer authorized to select an umpire if the appraisers fail to agree."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPERATION OF A COVERED AUTO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Driving a covered auto by an insured party."&lt;SEP&gt;"Driving a covered auto by the policyholder, a relative, or a rated resident."&lt;SEP&gt;"The act of driving a covered auto."&lt;SEP&gt;"The operation of a covered auto by the policyholder, a relative, or a rated resident is not subject to exclusion, even if the vehicle is leased or rented."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DEVICES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Devices are excluded from coverage if not permanently installed."&lt;SEP&gt;"Electronic or mechanical components added to a vehicle."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TELEPHONE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A telephone is included in the exclusion."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CLAIM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"EVENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A claim is a demand for damages covered under Part I, which the insurer may settle or defend."&lt;SEP&gt;"A claim is a formal request for payment under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"A request made by the policyholder to the insurer for payment under the terms of the policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f25ed079d4b7f6c7141fd78422f7f726</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEASED OR RENTED&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The act of leasing or renting a covered auto to others, which triggers the exclusion unless operated by the insured, a relative, or a rated resident."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MILEAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"AMOUNT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The number of miles a vehicle has been driven."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LAND MOTOR VEHICLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"VEHICLE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A motor vehicle used on land, which may be uninsured."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LIABLE PARTY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A liable party is a third party from whom the insured person may recover payments."&lt;SEP&gt;"The liable party is the source of payments that may be used for reimbursement."&lt;SEP&gt;"The liable party is the target of recovery efforts by the insured person."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-69d3b921f75f85252f4c9cdeaa3141bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APPRAISAL&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A formal process to determine the value of a loss when the insurer and policyholder disagree."&lt;SEP&gt;"A method to assess loss value in case of dispute."&lt;SEP&gt;"A process used to determine the value of a loss when there is a dispute between the insurer and the insured."&lt;SEP&gt;"A section outlining the process for resolving disputes over the value of a loss through an independent appraisal."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-e4f63404276c60a3d82c899176c55043&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e3e05ae8cb995bb756587490f5512f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SETTLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
