<node id="&quot;ADDITIONAL AUTO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"VEHICLE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An additional auto is a covered auto."&lt;SEP&gt;"An additional auto is a vehicle that will have the broadest coverage provided by the policy for any auto shown on the declarations page."&lt;SEP&gt;"An additional auto is a vehicle that, if insured more than 30 days after ownership, will have coverage beginning at the time of the request."&lt;SEP&gt;"An additional auto is a vehicle the policyholder becomes the owner of during the policy period, which does not permanently replace a vehicle listed on the declarations page, provided certain conditions are met."&lt;SEP&gt;"An additional auto is covered with the broadest coverage available for any auto listed on the declarations page."&lt;SEP&gt;"An auto acquired during the policy period that does not replace a listed vehicle, provided all conditions are met."&lt;SEP&gt;"Receives the broadest coverage available under the policy."</data>
