<node id="&quot;LIABILITY LIMITS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL_TERM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The maximum amount the insurer will pay for claims under Part III, subject to reductions based on other payments."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RIGHTS UNDER THIS POLICY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The legal and contractual rights of the insurer and policyholder, which remain intact even after agreeing to an appraisal."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PREMIUMS PAID&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PAYMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Amount paid to maintain the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Money paid by the insured to maintain coverage."&lt;SEP&gt;"Payments made by the insured for insurance coverage, which do not affect the limit of liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"The amount of premiums paid does not affect the limit of liability for medical payments under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The amount paid by the policyholder to maintain the insurance policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;FINITE USEFUL LIFE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ATTRIBUTE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A lifespan that is limited and not indefinite."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DIMINUTION OF VALUE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Diminution of value is a type of loss that is excluded from coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;OPPORTUNITY TO DEFEND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The insurer must be given the chance to defend the insured person to maintain coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SAME ELEMENTS OF DAMAGES&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The identical components of loss or injury, which cannot be compensated more than once."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APPEAL PROCESS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A formal procedure to challenge a claim denial."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AUTOMATIC TERMINATION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PROCESS"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Policy ends due to specific conditions."&lt;SEP&gt;"The policy automatically terminates if the renewal offer is not accepted."&lt;SEP&gt;"The policy ends automatically due to specific conditions, such as non-payment."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2e3e05ae8cb995bb756587490f5512f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PROCEDURE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Local rules of procedure apply to the arbitration process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PRIVATE PASSENGER&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"VEHICLE TYPE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A type of auto that is included in the definition of 'auto'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PERSONS OR ORGANIZATIONS LEGALLY RESPONSIBLE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LEGAL_ENTITY"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Entities that may be held legally liable for bodily injury and whose payments reduce the liability limits."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COVERED EMERGENCY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A covered emergency is a disablement resulting from mechanical or electrical breakdown, battery failure, insufficient supply of fuel, oil, water, or other fluid, flat tire, accidental lock-out, or entrapment in snow, mud, water, or sand within 100 feet of a road or highway."&lt;SEP&gt;"An unexpected event that triggers roadside assistance coverage, such as a vehicle breakdown."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cd680372852b670779cd9ab038f278e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;SPLIT LIMIT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"POLICY TERM"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A liability coverage structure where separate limits are set for 'each person', 'each accident', and 'property damage'."&lt;SEP&gt;"A type of coverage limit that separates the maximum payout per person and per accident."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EXTERNAL CRASH PARTS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"External crash parts are excluded from mechanical parts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Parts damaged in collisions, such as bumpers or fenders, which are excluded from mechanical parts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-245fa605e8e023a6acdcf8c36c35930e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"War, whether declared or undeclared, causes vehicle damage and is excluded."&lt;SEP&gt;"War, whether declared or undeclared, is an exclusion for coverage, as it may cause bodily injury or damage that is not covered under the policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;APPEAL BOND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An appeal bond is a financial guarantee required during an appeal, which the insurer may pay the premium for."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BODILY INJURY LIABILITY BOND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A financial guarantee required to cover bodily injury claims resulting from vehicle accidents; its absence defines a vehicle as uninsured."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;POST-REPAIR INSPECTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An evaluation of the vehicle after repairs are completed."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COVERAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A provision in the insurance policy that provides financial protection for specific types of losses."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage for an additional auto begins at the time of the request if reported after 30 days."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage is provided to all persons under the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the insurance protection provided for damages arising from accidents."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the insurance protection provided to the replacement auto, matching that of the auto it replaces, provided it is not covered by another policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the protection provided by the insurance policy, including Medical Payments Coverage, which is subject to limits and exclusions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the protection provided by the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage refers to the roadside assistance protection purchased for a vehicle."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage under Part I includes the duty to defend but is subject to exclusions."&lt;SEP&gt;"Coverage under the policy applies only if the accident or loss is promptly reported, regardless of fault or location of disablement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Protection provided by an insurance policy; it may be denied if an exclusion applies."&lt;SEP&gt;"Protection provided by the policy, which ceases for the deleted vehicle."&lt;SEP&gt;"The additional auto receives the broadest coverage provided by the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The additional auto will have the broadest coverage provided by the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The level of protection provided by the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The protection provided by the insurance policy for specified losses, such as damage to vehicles or custom parts."&lt;SEP&gt;"The protection provided by the insurance policy, which may be broadened during the policy period."&lt;SEP&gt;"The protection provided by the insurance policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The protection provided by the policy, which has a limit of liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"The protection provided by the policy."&lt;SEP&gt;"The scope of protection provided by the insurance policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20da18c34f7340c40297873edec25e72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e3e05ae8cb995bb756587490f5512f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69d3b921f75f85252f4c9cdeaa3141bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38c1857f7eddbd65f102ae432a80d4ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ac858e839dd324c4b80701da2b87bd7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2c04092b664c68f63780007564ef50d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cd680372852b670779cd9ab038f278e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55b66238ae6adb6999a975e6b7f7834c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f25ed079d4b7f6c7141fd78422f7f726</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EVIDENCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Local rules of evidence apply to the arbitration process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PICKUP BODY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"VEHICLE TYPE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A type of auto that is included in the definition of 'auto'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WORKERS' COMPENSATION LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LEGAL_REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A law that provides benefits to employees injured on the job, which reduces the available uninsured motorist coverage."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal framework that provides benefits to employees injured on the job."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;AUTHORIZED SERVICE REPRESENTATIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A service provider approved by the insurer to deliver roadside assistance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EACH PERSON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LIMIT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The maximum amount payable for bodily injury to one individual in a single accident, under a split limit."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount payable for bodily injury to one individual."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WHEELS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Rotating components of a vehicle, excluded from mechanical parts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Vehicle wheels that may be damaged and require repair or replacement."&lt;SEP&gt;"Wheels are excluded from mechanical parts."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-245fa605e8e023a6acdcf8c36c35930e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CIVIL WAR&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Civil war causes vehicle damage and is excluded."&lt;SEP&gt;"Civil war is a form of conflict that is excluded from coverage under the policy, as it may lead to injuries or damages not covered."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ATTACHMENT BOND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An attachment bond is a bond required to secure property during litigation, which the insurer may pay the premium for."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BODILY INJURY LIABILITY POLICY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An insurance policy that provides coverage for bodily injury caused by a vehicle; its absence at the time of an accident classifies the vehicle as uninsured."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;REPRESENTATIVE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A representative of the policyholder may accept or reject the renewal offer."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;ARBITRATORS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Arbitrators have no authority to award an amount exceeding the limit of liability."&lt;SEP&gt;"Two arbitrators must agree on a decision for it to be binding."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;CARGO VAN&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"VEHICLE TYPE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A type of auto that is included in the definition of 'auto'."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;DISABILITY BENEFITS LAW&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LEGAL_REGULATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A law that provides financial support to individuals unable to work due to disability, which reduces the available uninsured motorist coverage."&lt;SEP&gt;"A legal framework that provides financial support to individuals unable to work due to disability."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TOWING&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The service of moving a disabled vehicle to a repair facility."&lt;SEP&gt;"Towing a covered disabled auto to the nearest qualified repair facility is covered if performed by an unauthorized provider."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cd680372852b670779cd9ab038f278e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EACH ACCIDENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LIMIT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The maximum amount payable for bodily injury to two or more individuals in a single accident, subject to the 'each person' limit."&lt;SEP&gt;"The maximum amount payable for bodily injury to two or more people in a single accident."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAINT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Paint is excluded from mechanical parts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Surface coating on a vehicle, excluded from mechanical parts."&lt;SEP&gt;"The coating on the vehicle's surface that may be damaged and repaired as part of the restoration process."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-245fa605e8e023a6acdcf8c36c35930e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WARLIKE ACTION&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Warlike action by military forces is excluded."&lt;SEP&gt;"Warlike action by military forces of any government or authority, including actions to defend against an attack, is excluded from coverage."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BAIL BOND&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A bail bond is a financial guarantee required to secure release from custody after an accident involving bodily injury or property damage, and the insurer will pay up to $250."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;BONDING OR INSURING COMPANY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The entity providing a bodily injury liability bond or policy; if it denies coverage or becomes insolvent, the vehicle is considered uninsured."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMERGENCY FUEL DELIVERY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"SERVICE"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Delivery of fuel in case of a breakdown."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;TRANSFER OF INTEREST&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LEGAL CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The legal process by which ownership or rights under the policy are transferred."&lt;SEP&gt;"The transfer of rights under the policy."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-2e3e05ae8cb995bb756587490f5512f4</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RENEWAL PREMIUM&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL OBLIGATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Failure to pay the renewal premium on time means the offer is not accepted."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;LEGAL LIABILITY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"The legal liability of the operator or owner of an uninsured motor vehicle is determined by a binding decision of two arbitrators."&lt;SEP&gt;"The legal responsibility of the operator or owner of an uninsured vehicle for damages caused in an accident."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PUBLIC ROADS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"LOCATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"An auto is designed for operation principally upon public roads."&lt;SEP&gt;"Public roads are the designated pathways where trailers are designed to be towed."&lt;SEP&gt;"Roads open to public traffic; vehicles not used on them are excluded from the uninsured motor vehicle definition."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55b66238ae6adb6999a975e6b7f7834c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;PAYMENTS FOR BODILY INJURY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"FINANCIAL_TRANSACTION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Payments made due to bodily injury by or on behalf of legally responsible parties, which reduce the liability limits under Part III."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COVERED DISABLED AUTO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"A covered auto is one for which roadside assistance coverage has been purchased and that has sustained a covered emergency."&lt;SEP&gt;"A covered disabled auto is eligible for towing to the nearest qualified repair facility."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle covered under the policy that has become disabled and requires towing."&lt;SEP&gt;"A vehicle that is covered under the policy and has become disabled, qualifying for roadside assistance."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cd680372852b670779cd9ab038f278e</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;EMOTIONAL INJURY&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"CONCEPT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Psychological harm resulting from bodily injury to another person, which is covered under the 'each person' limit."&lt;SEP&gt;"Psychological harm resulting from bodily injury to another."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;WINDSHIELDS AND OTHER GLASS&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Glass components of a vehicle, excluded from mechanical parts."&lt;SEP&gt;"Glass components of the vehicle, including windshields, side windows, and rear windows, which may be damaged and repaired or replaced."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;MILITARY FORCE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"ORGANIZATION"</data>
  <data key="d4">"Military forces of any government, sovereign, or authority are involved in warlike actions."</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;$250&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"AMOUNT"</data>
