<node id="&quot;DECLARATIONS PAGE&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"DOCUMENT"</data>
  <data key="d4">The Declarations Page is a critical section of an insurance policy that serves as a summary of key policy details. It is a formal document that contains essential information about the policyholder, including the named insured, the insured’s address, and the underwriting company providing the insurance. The page lists covered vehicles, specifying both the auto being replaced and the replacement auto, as well as the stated amount for each covered auto. It outlines the coverages provided under the policy, such as liability coverage, uninsured/underinsured motorist protection, medical payments coverage, and coverage for non-owned autos. Key financial and limit-related information is clearly detailed, including coverage limits, the limit of liability for various coverages (such as for trailers), and the premium amount. The Declarations Page also includes the policy period, which defines the effective dates of coverage, and may list additional interests, such as lenders or other parties with a stake in the policy. Overall, the Declarations Page is a comprehensive document that summarizes the core elements of the insurance policy, often referred to as the Auto Insurance Coverage Summary, and serves as a foundational reference for understanding the scope and terms of the coverage.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-2e3e05ae8cb995bb756587490f5512f4&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-38c1857f7eddbd65f102ae432a80d4ea&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98ea72d43f9051dc6899f8d6aafcd9a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2c04092b664c68f63780007564ef50d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55b66238ae6adb6999a975e6b7f7834c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20da18c34f7340c40297873edec25e72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ac858e839dd324c4b80701da2b87bd7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-798fdf9e8255810d437349cea720f315&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f25ed079d4b7f6c7141fd78422f7f726</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;RATED RESIDENT&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">The term "RATED RESIDENT" refers to a person who resides in the same household as the policyholder and is considered for insurance rating purposes. This individual is typically listed on the insurance policy, may be included in the "Drivers and household residents" section of the declarations page, and is not designated as "Excluded" or "List Only." A rated resident is considered an insured person under the policy, subject to the same insurance rating as the policyholder, and may be involved in activities that affect the policy's terms, such as vehicle use. While the resident is not necessarily a relative, they are included in the risk assessment and may incur veterinary expenses if applicable. The presence of a rated resident can influence the policy's premium and coverage, particularly in relation to vehicle use—though their use of a vehicle not covered under the policy is generally excluded unless the vehicle is maintained or used by the insured. Importantly, a rated resident is exempt from the auto business exclusion when using a covered auto. However, exclusion from coverage may apply if the rated resident is convicted or pleads guilty to a criminal act or omission, particularly if they are involved in illegal activities that trigger policy exclusions. Overall, a rated resident is a household member whose status and behavior are factored into the insurance rating and coverage determination.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-20da18c34f7340c40297873edec25e72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-245fa605e8e023a6acdcf8c36c35930e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8918d81dfdf6055a12c8c1d621356d08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ea57b3201f9d42edca3669635573a74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f25ed079d4b7f6c7141fd78422f7f726</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;COVERED AUTO&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"OBJECT"</data>
  <data key="d4">The term "COVERED AUTO" refers to a vehicle that is explicitly included in an insurance policy and for which specific coverage has been purchased, making it eligible for protection under the policy’s terms. A covered auto includes any automobile or trailer listed on the declarations page, any additional auto, replacement auto, or trailer owned by the policyholder, and is subject to the policy’s provisions, including comprehensive coverage and loss payment under Part IV. These vehicles are insured under the policy, may be subject to a Stated Amount election, and are protected under Part III and Part IV of the policy, with coverage triggered when the vehicle is used with permission. 

A covered auto is primarily garaged in a specified location and may be transported between ports, but its use for commercial purposes triggers an exclusion. The vehicle is subject to the policy’s liability limit and is the only vehicle under the policy that provides coverage; other vehicles are excluded. Coverage applies when the vehicle is involved in a loss, and injury sustained while using it for certain purposes is excluded. 

Importantly, a covered auto is not covered if used in a personal vehicle sharing program or ride-sharing activity. Additionally, its use while leased, rented, or exchanged for compensation is excluded unless operated by the insured, a relative, or a rated resident. The vehicle is also subject to exclusions if used by a relative or rated resident not otherwise covered under the policy. 

Furthermore, a covered auto is a vehicle specifically included in the insurance policy, thereby excluded from the definition of an uninsured motor vehicle. It is a vehicle that is insured under the policy and qualifies for coverage, including when used with permission, which may extend insured status to the user. In cases where the vehicle is subject to a loan or lease agreement, the policyholder is legally obligated to pay upon total loss, subject to applicable deductions. Overall, a covered auto is a vehicle explicitly covered under the policy, with coverage governed by specific rules regarding liability, exclusions, and usage.</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-245fa605e8e023a6acdcf8c36c35930e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9fee7a00b84094770f04dcfe86a29e3a&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9cd680372852b670779cd9ab038f278e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-98ea72d43f9051dc6899f8d6aafcd9a5&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-e2c04092b664c68f63780007564ef50d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ea57b3201f9d42edca3669635573a74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-20da18c34f7340c40297873edec25e72&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8a3491a1885e53367b27b22e975a6fbb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-3bb98005a1307a094baa1b3869aeea6c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9ac858e839dd324c4b80701da2b87bd7&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-708cd65887876aa076b711ced7a4979e&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8918d81dfdf6055a12c8c1d621356d08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-33661b5c04aa1251a71c27b799dfbfc2&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-798fdf9e8255810d437349cea720f315&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f25ed079d4b7f6c7141fd78422f7f726</data>
</node>
<node id="&quot;INSURED PERSON&quot;">
  <data key="d0">entity</data>
  <data key="d3">"PERSON"</data>
  <data key="d4">The "INSURED PERSON" is an individual covered under an insurance policy who may receive benefits, including medical payments for injuries sustained in an accident, subject to policy exclusions and limits. This includes the policyholder ("you"), a relative, or a rated resident, as well as any person using a covered auto with permission from the policyholder, a relative, or a rated resident. The definition further extends to any person or organization legally liable for the acts or omissions of those individuals, and to any "Additional Interest" listed on the declarations page, limited to liability arising from the use of a covered auto. The insured person may be involved in an accident caused by an unidentified vehicle, sustain bodily injury, or be struck by a motor vehicle while not in a self-propelled vehicle, and remains eligible for coverage under the policy. They are entitled to benefits such as medical payments, and may recover damages from an uninsured motor vehicle, provided they comply with policy terms. The insured person is the recipient of payments and holds recovery rights, including the right to pursue recovery from another party, though this may require written consent from the insurer. They may also be required to sign a document agreeing to reimburse the insurer for payments made, particularly if a recovery is obtained from a liable party, and may instruct the insurer not to pursue recovery of the deductible. In the event of a claim, the insured person is involved in the determination of liability, and their residence may determine the location of arbitration. The insured person may agree to an alternate form of arbitration with the insurer and is subject to the policy’s arbitration provisions. The insurer cannot be made a party to a lawsuit to determine the liability of the insured, and the insured person’s bankruptcy or insolvency does not affect the insurer’s obligations. The insured person may incur attorney fees in recovering payment from a liable party, and the insurer shares responsibility for these fees. In certain circumstances, the insured person may be sued directly by the insurer for non-reimbursement of payments made. The policy may exclude coverage if the insured person is convicted or pleads guilty to a criminal act or omission, but such exclusion only applies upon a criminal conviction or plea. The insured person is not considered legally responsible for damages due to an accident unless specifically covered under the policy’s liability provisions, and may be required to pay prejudgment interest as part of damages awarded. Overall, the "INSURED PERSON" is a central figure in the insurance relationship, entitled to benefits and protections under the</data>
  <data key="d2">chunk-cc674f73d7a5cb327513cff560eedac9&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-69d3b921f75f85252f4c9cdeaa3141bb&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-8918d81dfdf6055a12c8c1d621356d08&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d016c8b9bbaa3c5bae4936f9d698a1c1&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-fb0aea7627d6cab63c56603774515efc&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ed4d5b68d5d2c5cb43c341277461c05d&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-cfb324337b8eb7e557e96d41d0a59527&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-6ea57b3201f9d42edca3669635573a74&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-d2d8f56664f7ecfe69d0c03f4f89540c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-9d1b4fcafc6c7d7efe5c322ad9bd33fd&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-ba971e62cee92a6aaf201ec7e51cf087&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-55b66238ae6adb6999a975e6b7f7834c&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-798fdf9e8255810d437349cea720f315&lt;SEP&gt;chunk-f67c7ff74642b092b6581278092146d7</data>
</node>
